| Iterator                           | Generator                      |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Uses `__iter__()` and `__next__()` | Uses `yield`                   |
| More code                          | Less code                      |
| Manual implementation              | Automatic implementation       |
| Harder to write                    | Easier to write                |
| Returns values using `next()`      | Generates values using `yield` |



yield in Python

yield is a keyword used inside a function to make it a generator.



| `return`                                | `yield`                               |
| --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Ends the function immediately           | Pauses the function                   |
| Returns a single value                  | Returns values one by one             |
| Function cannot continue after `return` | Function resumes from where it paused |
| Used in normal functions                | Used in generator functions           |
| Stores all results if needed            | Generates results lazily (on demand)  |
